ase containing child actions."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that will be invoked with child actions against presented child"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"state."}]}],"name":"destination"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The fileID."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"fileID"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The filePath.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"filePath"},{"name":"line","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The line."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The column.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"column"}]},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This version of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ifLet"},{"text":" requires the usage of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Presents()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" macro and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction","isActive":true},{"text":" type in your feature’s domain.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if a parent feature holds onto a piece of optional child state, then it can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"perform its core logic "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the child’s logic by using the "},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" operator:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  @ObservableState","  struct State {","    @Presents var child: Child.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(PresentationAction<Child.Action>)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some ReducerOf<Self> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifLet(\\.$child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" operator does a number of things to make integrating parent and child features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ergonomic and enforce correctness:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction\/dismiss","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent, it runs the parent feature"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"before the child state is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’d out. This gives the parent feature an opportunity to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"inspect the child state one last time before the state is cleared.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction\/presented(_:)"},{"text":" action is sent it runs the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the parent feature to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":"’d","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automatically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":"s out child state when an action is sent for alerts and confirmation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dialogs.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It gives the child feature access to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DismissEffect","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" dependency, which allows the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"child feature to dismiss itself without communicating with the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/ifLet(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-4ub6q"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Ephemeral state","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/ifLet(_:action:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-3ux09"],"anchor":"Ephemeral-state"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationState","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction","doc: